            <p>
                Caring for your new arrival over the coming days will be a full time job. Moving home is extremely stressful for your cat or dog. His entire life will be turned upside down and he'll naturally turn to you for comfort and support! 
            </p>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <p> <span>Proper Nutrition</span> : Feed your cat a balanced and appropriate diet to meet their nutritional needs. Provide fresh water at all times and monitor their weight to prevent obesity-related health issues.
                        Litter Box Maintenance: Keep your cat's litter box clean by scooping it daily and replacing the litter regularly. Cats are clean animals and may stop using a dirty litter box, leading to behavior problems.</p>
                </li>
